dct_description_sm: "Entered in Sta. Hall London. & according to act of Congress, in the year 1857, by H.D. Rogers, in the Clerk's Office of the District Court of Massachusetts." In upper left margin: "Atlas of United States &c." In upper right margin: "13." Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. Shows counties of Utah stretching from California into contemporary Colorado, Fillmore as the capitol, and "proposed Pacific Railway routes in purple." Includes notes. Plate 13 from: Atlas of the United States of North America / by Henry Darwin Rogers and A. Keith Johnston. London : J. Murray, 1857.
